The paper discusses techniques for improving the efficiency and accuracy of formula-based debugging, which is a software engineering topic. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions exploring relevant parts of a program, which suggests a focus on program analysis and verification, placing it in the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The use of statistical fault-localization information suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence, placing it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses scalability, which is a systems engineering concern, placing it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions logical reasoning, which suggests a connection to logic and constraint programming, placing it in the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category.
